metadata.name: Duffy was
metadata.description:
in the NCAA, but at Marquette, he was the king of the people.



You don't have what it takes to make Marquette's 12-man roster.



Duffy, as the king of the road, played NCAA games like this, others need to think about their own options.



The good news is that while there was a lot of watching and a lot less participation, there were some very good players this year.



"Todd TOWNSEND, 2.01 METRES TALL, SEEMS TO HAVE A PRETTY GOOD SKILL SET AND CAN DO EVERYTHING."
